## Controllers and Endpoints
- Keep controllers thin; delegate to services.
- Use attribute routing; version APIs explicitly.
- Return appropriate status codes and problem details.

## Validation and Mapping
- Use FluentValidation or data annotations; validate at the edges.
- Map DTOs with explicit profiles (e.g., AutoMapper) where helpful.

## Security
- Enforce authentication and authorization via policies.
- Validate inputs; protect against injection and over-posting.

## Observability
- Structured logging with correlation IDs.
- Health checks and readiness/liveness endpoints.

## Testing
- Unit test services; integration test endpoints.

## Validation Checklist
- [ ] Controllers thin; business logic in services
- [ ] Validation at boundaries; DTOs clean
- [ ] AuthZ policies enforced; least privilege
- [ ] Logs/health checks implemented
- [ ] Integration tests cover critical paths

